NAME
    Attr/Boolean -- implement boolean attribute

DESCRIPTION
    Attribute object is true if it exists as a regular file, otherwise
    it is false.  Valid values for the *set* and *is* methods are 'true'
    or 'false'.

METHODS
    get     -- print attribute value to stdout
    set     -- set the attribute to the given value, true or false
    is      -- assert attribute has the given value, true or false
    help    -- display this help screen

